        evaluate:   "Evaluate the following claim: 'Root hair cells are the most important cells in the root because they perform all the water and ion absorption.' Identify what is correct in this claim, what it omits, and provide a more complete account of how water and ion absorption is distributed across root structures.",
        create:     "Propose an experiment to determine whether aquaporins or ion channels are the primary route for water uptake into root hair cells under conditions of high transpiration demand. Your proposal must specify: the inhibitors or genetic knockouts you would use, how you would measure water flux specifically in root hair cells, appropriate controls, and how you would interpret each possible result."
