        analyze:    "Cross-sections of roots from three unnamed plant species are described: Species A — large central xylem vessel, thick Casparian strip, dense cortex, no aerenchyma. Species B — extensive aerenchyma in cortex (>40% air space), multiple small xylem vessels, thin cortex. Species C — no root hairs, dense velamen (multiple-layered epidermis with dead air-filled cells), minimal cortex. Analyse the probable habitat of each species and justify your deduction using specific structural features.",
