        apply:      "A farmer is planning to grow chickpeas (a legume) in a field that has not grown legumes for 20 years. Predict whether Rhizobium inoculation of the seed is advisable, explain your reasoning, and describe what observable evidence the farmer could use 6 weeks after planting to assess whether nitrogen fixation is occurring.",
        analyze:    "Mycorrhizal colonisation data from three forest plots are: Plot 1 (no fertiliser): 85% root colonisation, 45 kg P/ha available. Plot 2 (moderate P): 60% colonisation, 90 kg P/ha available. Plot 3 (high P): 12% colonisation, 180 kg P/ha available. Analyse the relationship between phosphorus availability and mycorrhizal colonisation, identify the mechanism responsible, and predict what will happen to Plot 3 trees if phosphate application stops after three years.",
        evaluate:   "Evaluate the proposed global application of Striga (witchweed) biocontrol using mycorrhizal fungi, given that mycorrhizal colonisation of Striga's host crop can reduce Striga infection. Your evaluation must address: the ecological evidence base, potential unintended consequences for non-target organisms, practical and economic feasibility, and whether this represents a sustainable strategy.",
        create:     "Construct a fully annotated diagram of a mature, active soybean root nodule. Your diagram must include and label: the nodule cortex, bacteroids, symbiosome membrane, leghemoglobin location, site of N₂ fixation, site of NH₃ assimilation, direction of carbon (malate) delivery from plant, and direction of fixed nitrogen export to plant. Add a brief annotation explaining the function of each labelled component."
