        apply:      "A deer population has r = 0.6 yr⁻¹ and K = 800. Using dN/dt = rN(1 − N/K), calculate dN/dt when: (a) N = 100; (b) N = 400; (c) N = 700; (d) N = 800. Sketch the resulting S-shaped growth curve on labelled axes. Mark K and the point of maximum growth rate on your sketch.",
