        evaluate:   "A fisheries scientist recommends harvesting a stock at N = K/2 to achieve maximum sustainable yield. A commercial fishing company argues that since the population is at N = 0.9K, there is 'plenty of room to harvest' and proposes taking 30% of current stock annually. Evaluate the company's proposal — use the logistic growth equation to calculate actual growth rate at N = 0.9K, determine whether a 30% annual harvest is sustainable at this population size, and explain what would happen to the population over five years if this harvest rate were applied.",
