        analyze:    "Two HIV-positive patients are reviewed. Patient A: on ART for 2 years, viral load undetectable, CD4 count 190 cells/μL. Patient B: not on ART, viral load 8,000 copies/mL, CD4 count 210 cells/μL. Analyse the immunological situation of each patient. Determine who is at greater risk of opportunistic infection and justify your reasoning. Explain why viral load and CD4 count can dissociate in this way, and what each parameter independently tells you about the patient's situation.",
