        apply:      "A plant's light reactions are producing ATP and NADPH in a 2:1 ratio (instead of the ideal 3:2) due to a mutation in the cytochrome b6f complex. Predict which stage of the Calvin cycle will be rate-limited first and calculate how many turns of the cycle could complete before NADPH becomes the bottleneck, given a starting supply of 18 ATP and 12 NADPH.",
