        evaluate:   "A biotechnology company proposes to increase crop yield by overexpressing G3P dehydrogenase in wheat to accelerate the reduction stage. Evaluate whether this strategy is likely to increase net carbon fixation, with reference to the stoichiometric constraints of the Calvin cycle, the availability of NADPH, and the likely effect on RuBP regeneration.",
        create:     "Derive the full stoichiometric equation for Calvin cycle glucose synthesis (6 CO₂ → 1 glucose) from first principles, building up from the single-turn stoichiometry. Show each stage's ATP and NADPH contributions per turn, multiply for six turns, and justify why the final equation is 6 CO₂ + 18 ATP + 12 NADPH → C₆H₁₂O₆ + 18 ADP + 18 Pᵢ + 12 NADP⁺. Identify and account for the water molecules."
