        evaluate:   "Evaluate the claim: 'Light reactions are the most important stage of photosynthesis because they produce the energy.' Identify what is accurate and what is imprecise in this statement. Clarify what form of energy is produced, what it is used for, and why the distinction between light capture and carbon fixation matters for a complete understanding.",
        create:     "Design an experiment using isolated chloroplasts to demonstrate that ATP and NADPH are produced by light reactions independently of CO₂ fixation. Specify: (a) how you would isolate and verify intact chloroplasts; (b) how you would measure ATP and NADPH production; (c) what light and dark controls you would include; (d) what result would confirm that light reactions alone are sufficient to produce both products; (e) how you would rule out contamination from broken chloroplasts or mitochondria."
