        evaluate:   "A student states that 'PSI is more important than PSII because it produces NADPH, which is the actual reducing agent used in the Calvin cycle.' Evaluate this claim. Assess the relative contributions of each photosystem, identify what each uniquely provides, and explain why neither can function without the other in non-cyclic photophosphorylation.",
        create:     "Design an experiment to determine whether a novel plant extract inhibits PSII, PSI, or the cytochrome b6f complex. Specify: (a) three separate measurements you would make and what each would indicate; (b) the pattern of results expected if each of the three components were the inhibitor's target; (c) the controls required; (d) how you would distinguish a direct inhibitor of the ETC from a compound that simply uncouples the proton gradient from ATP synthesis."
